Durban - Verulam police are investigating cases of murder and attempted murder after a woman was killed and her boyfriend seriously injured in a shooting at Cottonlands, north of Durban. The incident took place on Friday.  Security company Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) said that at 6:49pm, a silver Toyota Etios sped into the Rusa premises in Verulam. A 23-year-old man in the vehicle said he had been shot. The man had gunshot wounds to his abdomen, both hands and his head, Rusa said. “The victim said he was at his girlfriend’s residence when two unknown suspects forced their way into the house and shot them without warning. They then searched him for valuables before fleeing empty handed. “The man informed Rusa members that his girlfriend was also shot, however he could not confirm if she was still alive.” Rusa said its reaction officers proceeded to the woman’s residence in Cottonlands.  The company said the 28-year-old woman was found in a prone position on the bed. She had been shot several times in the head, neck and back.  “She showed no signs of life and was declared deceased. Several spent 9mm cartridges were located in the room.” Police spokesperson Constable Thenjiswa Ngcobo confirmed that a case had been opened. “On July 15, Verulam police were called to Cottonlands near a store. On arrival they were shown a body of a female with multiple gunshot wounds. It is alleged that the deceased was with a male who also sustained gunshot wounds and was rushed to hospital. A case of murder and attempted murder are being investigated by Verulam SAPS.” THE MERCURY